caption: Great staff and great food. Veggie Burger is amazing. They offer inside sitting now -  each table separated from another with plastic dividers. Order over the phone and pick up in store fast and easy. Staff is very attentive. Thumbs up.

I really like Bareburger and their gluten free items.  I've been to other Bareburgers and have really enjoyed my experience.  This was my first time visiting the court st location.  I placed my order at 12:17pm and didn't receive my food until 12:52 pm.  Apparently there was a big order placed and my order was placed to the side.  I had to approach the employee to get this information after waiting for 30 minutes.  Had I not wasted almost my entire lunch hour waiting, I would've demanded my money back and left without eating.  The food was hot and good when I finally ate it, but not worth that type of wait.

The food was flavorful and fresh. The sweet potato fries and onion rings were delicious but came out cold. Had a Wrangler Burger without the Bun and everything was good from the bacon to the meat. Be warned that they charge an 18% auto gratuity on take out orders.

The chicken wings were completely raw inside. The Caesar salad I ordered arrived with gross tomatoes and chopped AMERICAN CHEESE. Yuck. The problem is that you pay before you get the food so there went $50 down the drain. They also don’t provide any water for patrons, only overpriced bottled wate.  In addition, We BOTH suffered from major digestion issues for over 12 hours after eating there. I’m so upset. Can’t believe this place IS NOTHING LIKE WHAT IT USED TO BE.

No one ever asked if the food was good or if we needed anything else.  Then, our patience was really running out when waiting another like 10 min to get someone’s attention for the check (we have no idea who’s responsible for waiting tables at this time), while there’s employees walking around minding their own business, someone cleaning up on the other side of the bar, and several employees look like they are chitchatting in front of the kitchen. I hate to be like “you can’t chat and have fun at work”, but it wasn’t a very good experience to be ignored, even if they were understaffed.

Bareburger is a local New York chain with a lot of vegan & healthy options. I went to this location recently and was very impressed with their vegan menu: they have a bunch of different burgers or you can construct your own, and they have a really good variety of types of patty and toppings. Everything on the menu has calorie and nutrient counts listed so this is a great choice if you're trying to watch out for that. I've tried both the "Original" (an Impossible burger) and the "Wake Up Call" (a beyond burger) off their vegan menu and both were well thought out and delicious. The service here is okay and the prices are Brooklyn normal - we paid something like $30 for two burgers without sides or drinks.
